# flutter-development

ARCH: follow `.cursor/rules/architecture-governance.mdc`; Flutter convenience patterns do not bypass DI/boundary/pattern-fit gates
WIDGET: composition>inheritance; immutable inputs(final/const); build() side-effect free
STATE: setState for local UI only; shared/business state outside widget
ASYNC: prefer async/await over then/catchError chains
NULL: avoid ! unless proven by control flow
QUALITY: keep formatter/lints clean; behavior changes require tests
TYPE_DOC: classes/mixins/extensions start with `///` role/purpose; skip only if trivial and obvious from name+path
PUBLIC_API_DOC: add `///` when contract/side-effects/threading are non-obvious
INLINE_DOC: `//` or short `///` for algorithm/protocol/platform/perf/invariant details not obvious from code
DOC_TONE: explain why/invariant; never narrate obvious line-by-line actions
SRP: one reason to change per unit; if a type mixes concerns, extract focused collaborators
SRP_UI_LOGIC: keep pure rules (layout/validation/parsing/protocol) out of build() and usually out of State
SRP_VISUAL_INTERACTION: split painter/layout-only widgets from gesture/drag/session state when non-trivial
SRP_DATA_IO: separate connection lifecycle/subscriptions from domain framing when mixed code hurts tests/reuse
SRP_NAMING: prefer local suffix conventions (*_page.dart,*_controller.dart,*_repository.dart,*_service.dart,*_painter.dart,*_session.dart)
SRP_TRIGGER: split when file navigation is hard, reasons-to-change diverge, or pure-unit testing is blocked by heavy widget/mocking needs